In relation to the aforementioned questions, the course will cover climate, biomes, species richness, biotic interactions, diversity of animals (excursion in Zoology museum) and plants (excursion in Botanical gardens), human impact on tropical ecosystems, and tropical research methods. The format of the course will be lectures, excursions, group assignments, reading and presenting scientific papers, and discussions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduce tropical biology and research in the tropics. The course will be structured around the following questions; What is different about tropical biology? How has tropical biology contributed to important advancements in Biology? How does tropical biology work in practice? Which threats do tropical species face?Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Have a better understanding of tropical biota, and further develop skills in collecting information from the internet and scientific literature, reading scientific papers, oral presentation, and group work.
